WEBVTT

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:10.370
(This drama is based on
the 2018 cryptocurrency market.)

00:00:10.370 --> 00:00:11.670
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

00:00:11.670 --> 00:00:12.840
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:18.410
What is it? What's wrong?

00:00:20.850 --> 00:00:22.050
Look at this...

00:00:24.420 --> 00:00:26.060
(Enderion minus 30.01 percent)

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:36.830
(Episode 10: Our Share)

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.540
Following the cyber hacking incident
at Equalus Cryptocurrency Exchange,

00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:42.870
investor sentiment has
cooled dramatically.

00:00:43.410 --> 00:00:46.010
As major cryptocurrencies
continue their downward trend,

00:00:46.180 --> 00:00:48.710
Enderion has also taken a downturn.

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:52.180
In just a few days, Enderion has
plummeted by nearly 30 percent.

00:00:52.550 --> 00:00:54.080
- It went up!
- What?

00:00:54.350 --> 00:00:55.750
- It did?
- Really?

00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:57.190
The cost of living went up again.

00:00:57.850 --> 00:00:58.860
Darn it.

00:00:58.920 --> 00:01:01.690
Darn it, it dropped.
That girl, I swear.

00:01:02.490 --> 00:01:03.930
- It's up.
- Really?

00:01:04.330 --> 00:01:05.530
How much?

00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:07.800
My body fat is up from last year.

00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:08.830
Why you...

00:01:09.870 --> 00:01:11.500
It dropped again.

00:01:18.010 --> 00:01:19.140
It's up.

00:01:19.140 --> 00:01:20.480
- How much?
- It went up?

00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:22.980
Your daily fortune.

00:01:24.910 --> 00:01:27.220
Hey. You're doing that on purpose,
aren't you?

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:30.790
Come on. Crypto is 70 percent luck
and 30 percent skill.

00:01:31.020 --> 00:01:32.920
At this point,
we might as well check our fortunes.

00:01:33.090 --> 00:01:34.220
What's your zodiac sign?

00:01:34.860 --> 00:01:35.860
The Dragon.

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:37.760
Let's see, Dragon...

00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:40.530
Here it is.
"Misfortunes never come alone."

00:01:40.530 --> 00:01:41.900
Sounds like a good one, right?

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:43.900
"Even if you fall backward,
you'll break your nose..."

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:47.800
Let's just eat.

00:01:48.140 --> 00:01:49.140
Why you...

00:01:49.610 --> 00:01:50.610
Eun Sang.

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:53.310
- Shouldn't we just pull out?
- What?

00:01:53.310 --> 00:01:56.250
Come on.
It's already dropped by 30 percent.

00:01:57.550 --> 00:01:58.750
She's right.

00:01:58.750 --> 00:02:01.180
It has been
dropping for a few days now.

00:02:01.650 --> 00:02:02.650
Are you crazy?

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:05.520
We'd be fools if we pulled out now.

00:02:05.790 --> 00:02:07.260
What if it drops even more?

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:10.890
Sometimes you just have to
ride out the storm.

00:02:11.660 --> 00:02:15.260
If you worry about the day-to-day,
you'll never make the big bucks.

00:02:15.900 --> 00:02:19.240
So let's just hold steady
and see this through, okay?

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:22.310
Let's talk about something else.

00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:23.840
Anyone have some good news?

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:26.840
Right. Don't you have
anything interesting to share?

00:02:28.780 --> 00:02:29.780
You got nothing?

00:02:33.380 --> 00:02:36.020
So you're finally letting me
join the conversation?

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:37.890
Now that the mood
has gotten this awkward?

00:02:38.120 --> 00:02:40.460
Fine, you're in.
Go ahead, say literally anything.

00:02:40.620 --> 00:02:41.690
What is there to say...

00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:47.600
Autumn will be here soon,
and the leaves will be falling.

00:02:47.660 --> 00:02:49.730
Anything but things falling.
Talk about something else.

00:02:50.030 --> 00:02:51.700
Da Hae,
your button is about to fall off.

00:02:52.640 --> 00:02:56.310
I heard you were
quitting the company.

00:02:56.310 --> 00:02:57.340
Is that true?

00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:00.280
That's just a rumor.

00:03:00.540 --> 00:03:03.310
Why would Dr. Ham quit a job
that's going so well?

00:03:03.450 --> 00:03:06.180
He can make 500,000 dollars
in bonuses just for showing up.

00:03:06.320 --> 00:03:08.750
You keep throwing around
"500,000 dollars..."

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:11.950
I didn't mean to offend you.

00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:13.320
It's 600,000 dollars.

00:03:14.290 --> 00:03:15.290
How annoying.

00:03:16.290 --> 00:03:18.690
- What a turn-off.
- Stop saying "drop!"

00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:24.030
Thank you for the meal.

00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:25.400
Thank you.

00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:27.500
Gosh, I'm stuffed.

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:30.040
We could've just split the bill.

00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:31.370
Those who got all worked up,

00:03:31.370 --> 00:03:33.380
demanding to know
who ate the pricey stir-fry...

00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:35.140
when we were about
to split the bill,

00:03:35.510 --> 00:03:36.880
shouldn't be complaining. Right?

00:03:37.610 --> 00:03:41.020
Our finances were a little tight
for a fancy dish like that.

00:03:41.320 --> 00:03:43.590
- Why? Is something wrong?
- It's just that...

00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:48.520
The crypto market has been
tanking lately.

00:03:49.090 --> 00:03:51.190
So everyone's been on edge.

00:03:51.460 --> 00:03:53.560
- I thought it was serious.
- "Something serious?"

00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:56.670
This might not be a big deal to you,
Dr. Ham.

00:03:56.730 --> 00:03:59.170
- Want to get some ice cream?
- I'm getting chocolate.

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.210
Right.

00:04:05.040 --> 00:04:08.180
Are you sure everything is
all right with you?

00:04:08.680 --> 00:04:10.680
That whole thing
about you quitting...

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:13.450
Hoppang Bite was just talking
nonsense, right?

00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:14.580
How many times must I tell you?

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:17.720
Workers talk about lunch
or quitting.

00:04:18.120 --> 00:04:20.490
You shouldn't get worked up
over every little rumor.

00:04:21.420 --> 00:04:22.430
Okay, fine then.

00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:25.090
So...

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:27.830
about Jung Da Hee.

00:04:29.270 --> 00:04:30.570
What's she like?

00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:32.100
Da Hee?

00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:33.940
Why?

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:36.840
What? No reason.

00:04:37.970 --> 00:04:39.440
What? With Da Hee?

00:04:40.510 --> 00:04:43.080
- Do what with her?
- The snack subscription box.

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:46.480
The launch deadline is tight,
so you'll need someone to help you.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:51.050
So I want you and Da Hee
to work together on it.

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:52.420
What do you say?

00:04:52.420 --> 00:04:55.560
Yes.
I'll do my best to help, Da Hee.

00:04:55.960 --> 00:04:56.960
Oh...

00:04:58.530 --> 00:04:59.530
Okay.

00:05:07.540 --> 00:05:11.510
Mr. Ko said you needed help,
so I volunteered.

00:05:11.810 --> 00:05:14.040
You must be thrown off
by my arrival.

00:05:14.040 --> 00:05:15.850
No, not at all.

00:05:16.410 --> 00:05:18.080
I'm looking forward
to working with you.

00:05:18.450 --> 00:05:19.450
Okay.

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.820
Oh, about that letter...

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:25.190
The letter?

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:28.420
I mentioned it only to you...

00:05:28.690 --> 00:05:30.990
that I'd put a letter
in your locker.

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:33.600
About that...

00:05:35.100 --> 00:05:36.230
I'm sorry.

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:39.040
- What for?
- The thing is, about that letter...

00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:41.100
I'm the one who took it.

00:05:41.500 --> 00:05:43.110
You did?

00:05:43.770 --> 00:05:44.770
Yes.

00:05:45.370 --> 00:05:49.150
But can we leave it
at that for today?

00:05:49.780 --> 00:05:52.280
I have my reasons,
which I can't explain just yet.

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:54.750
This must be a big shock for you.

00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:57.850
No. I wasn't trying
to interrogate you or anything.

00:05:58.190 --> 00:05:59.190
I'm sorry.

00:06:00.120 --> 00:06:02.960
But to be honest,
I was a little surprised too.

00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:05.730
I took the envelope,

00:06:06.060 --> 00:06:07.460
but it was just an empty envelope.

00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:10.070
The letter itself was gone.

00:06:11.070 --> 00:06:13.640
I threw it away.

00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:16.340
- You what?
- It was an accident.

00:06:17.240 --> 00:06:19.180
I feel so terrible, I'm so sorry.

00:06:25.450 --> 00:06:26.950
Don't worry about it.

00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:28.720
But still...

00:06:29.450 --> 00:06:30.750
Are you busy, Da Hee?

00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:32.290
Let me buy you a meal,

00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:34.890
or at least a coffee.

00:06:34.890 --> 00:06:36.590
I feel too guilty
leaving it like this.

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:39.760
And I'm worried you might get
the wrong idea about me.

00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:42.100
No, not at all.
There's nothing to misunderstand.

00:06:43.030 --> 00:06:45.070
I actually have plans today.

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:46.970
Let's get coffee another time.

00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:04.320
(Notice on Interim
Severance Pay Application)

00:07:10.060 --> 00:07:12.330
Looks like applications are open
for severance pay.

00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:14.400
Yes.

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.970
On the 73rd National Liberation Day,
President Moon Jae In...

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:26.680
stated true liberation means peace
on the Korean Peninsula.

00:07:28.510 --> 00:07:31.550
You're struggling as is
and have another mouth to feed.

00:07:31.550 --> 00:07:33.380
Why would you make
side dishes for me?

00:07:33.450 --> 00:07:37.290
Your dad just eats the leftovers.
Don't worry about it.

00:07:37.490 --> 00:07:40.390
Hey, I'm fine with leftovers.

00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:42.530
How's your back?

00:07:42.590 --> 00:07:46.130
Gosh, my back's a little sore
from lying down all the time.

00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:47.560
I was asking Mom.

00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:52.270
Oh, I shouldn't have spoken.

00:07:52.270 --> 00:07:53.640
It's the same as usual.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:55.940
It actually feels better
when I move around,

00:07:56.710 --> 00:07:58.540
and it's a lot easier to walk.

00:07:59.680 --> 00:08:03.280
But you can't exactly move around
when you're driving all day.

00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:05.150
She won't be doing that much longer.

00:08:05.150 --> 00:08:07.350
- Her boss wants her to retire...
- Will you be quiet?

00:08:08.420 --> 00:08:09.420
What's going on?

00:08:10.250 --> 00:08:11.250
Mom, are you retiring?

00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:12.790
No.

00:08:13.390 --> 00:08:16.030
- Just eat your apple.
- Seriously, are you retiring?

00:08:16.860 --> 00:08:18.090
No,

00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:20.530
they reduced the number
of bus routes,

00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:22.000
so management asked...

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:23.930
if I'd be willing
to take some time off.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:25.670
They were just testing the waters.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:29.510
- What? Isn't that the same thing?
- I said no, it's not like that.

00:08:30.640 --> 00:08:31.640
Besides,

00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:34.440
if I retire, I have no intention
of depending on you.

00:08:34.640 --> 00:08:36.750
Who's worried about that?

00:08:36.910 --> 00:08:40.020
Then stop making that face
and eat your apple. Okay?

00:08:42.550 --> 00:08:45.120
- You have some too, Mom.
- Of course I will.

00:08:47.820 --> 00:08:49.790
Why are you eating the bruised spot?

00:08:49.790 --> 00:08:51.660
It's fine. I'll cut the bruise out.

00:08:51.730 --> 00:08:52.730
Darn it.

00:08:53.030 --> 00:08:54.730
You should be
cutting something else out.

00:08:59.970 --> 00:09:03.270
Gosh, I don't get why
people even eat apples.

00:09:16.290 --> 00:09:18.350
(Enderion)

00:09:18.790 --> 00:09:21.660
Darn it,
should I really just sell now?

00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:24.190
I should salvage what I can
for Mom's living expenses.

00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:28.960
But everyone said I'd be a fool
to sell now.

00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:34.200
Maybe if I put in a little more
at this price...

00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:37.310
What?

00:09:37.770 --> 00:09:41.040
Only a ship that weathers the storm
can reach the farthest seas.

00:09:41.210 --> 00:09:43.550
Unwavering faith brings
a great reward.

00:09:44.280 --> 00:09:45.380
- Da Hae, that's your horoscope
- What is this?

00:09:45.380 --> 00:09:46.380
for the month.

00:09:46.380 --> 00:09:48.420
Of all the times,
she has to send this.

00:09:51.490 --> 00:09:52.690
Fine.

00:09:52.690 --> 00:09:55.560
Why should my mom eat bruised fruit?

00:10:00.200 --> 00:10:01.200
Okay.

00:10:02.160 --> 00:10:04.270
All right. Let's do this.

00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:08.070
I'll cash out my severance pay
and put it into crypto.

00:10:11.070 --> 00:10:13.210
(I'll cash out my severance pay
and put it into crypto.)

00:10:17.510 --> 00:10:18.510
Hi.

00:10:19.250 --> 00:10:22.350
I was told my severance pay
came through.

00:10:22.920 --> 00:10:24.890
I'm Jung Da Hae
from the Marketing Team.

00:10:25.190 --> 00:10:26.190
Yes.

00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:31.030
First, could you please sign
the confirmation form?

00:10:31.590 --> 00:10:32.600
Sure.

00:10:34.330 --> 00:10:35.730
(Severance Pay
Acknowledgment of Receipt)

00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:38.330
By the way, are you and Eun Sang
doing something together?

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:41.340
Eun Sang? Why do you ask?

00:10:41.470 --> 00:10:42.970
Ms. Eun Sang just collected...

00:10:42.970 --> 00:10:44.270
her severance pay
a little while ago.

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:47.080
And now you're applying
for yours too,

00:10:47.510 --> 00:10:49.410
so I just figured you two
were doing something together.

00:10:49.680 --> 00:10:52.050
Eun Sang applied for
her severance pay too?

00:10:53.420 --> 00:10:56.750
You didn't know?
I assumed you knew, being so close.

00:10:59.590 --> 00:11:00.590
You're all set.

00:11:01.890 --> 00:11:04.160
Enderion is reeling from
a string of bad news,

00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:07.030
plummeting more than fifty percent
from its peak.

00:11:07.830 --> 00:11:11.000
Financial experts warn that
if the current downtrend continues,

00:11:11.070 --> 00:11:15.040
it could trigger a market crash,
raising serious concerns.

00:11:15.100 --> 00:11:18.040
Wasn't this crypto on a bull run
just a little while ago?

00:11:18.110 --> 00:11:20.210
- What's going on?
- Crypto, sir.

00:11:20.310 --> 00:11:22.780
- Nevertheless, Enderion...
- This stuff!

00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:26.450
I heard someone
supposedly made a million off this.

00:11:26.580 --> 00:11:28.580
Gosh, and now look at it.
It's tanked.

00:11:28.980 --> 00:11:31.390
A million dollars is a huge amount,
isn't it?

00:11:31.490 --> 00:11:32.920
I wish people
who made that much money...

00:11:32.920 --> 00:11:35.660
had to wear a name tag or something.

00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:38.190
- Why's that?
- So I can mooch a coffee off them.

00:11:38.590 --> 00:11:39.930
Would you like some coffee?

00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:41.730
- What?
- Why are you offering?

00:11:41.800 --> 00:11:43.870
- I also hit ten...
- You made a million dollars?

00:11:46.800 --> 00:11:48.570
punches.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.410
I got ten punches on my coffee card.

00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:54.710
- Excuse me, Eun Sang?
- Oh! You startled me.

00:11:55.880 --> 00:11:56.910
Yes.

00:11:57.080 --> 00:11:59.980
I'm sorry.
I just came to buy a bandage.

00:12:00.050 --> 00:12:01.550
Sure. Just a moment.

00:12:04.290 --> 00:12:05.620
(Enderion)

00:12:10.890 --> 00:12:12.230
It keeps dropping...

00:12:13.130 --> 00:12:14.860
It's dropping like a rock...

00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:19.440
This feels like
a major unlucky streak.

00:12:24.570 --> 00:12:27.880
Tell me, oh wise one,
what does my future hold?

00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:31.310
(Father)

00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:38.720
Oh my gosh.

00:12:39.150 --> 00:12:41.490
Ma'am, what is it with you now?

00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:43.830
If you're going to be this dramatic,
just go get a boyfriend.

00:12:44.090 --> 00:12:45.360
It's the crypto.

00:12:45.560 --> 00:12:47.160
I haven't slept a wink.

00:12:48.160 --> 00:12:50.900
I sold off my bags, my shoes,
and all my precious babies...

00:12:50.900 --> 00:12:51.930
to buy crypto.

00:12:51.930 --> 00:12:53.570
But the price just keeps tanking.

00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:55.200
Gosh, well,

00:12:55.800 --> 00:12:58.870
getting rid of your precious babies
was a good call, but...

00:12:59.370 --> 00:13:01.340
Just live your realistic life.

00:13:01.340 --> 00:13:03.610
Losing sleep and skipping meals...

00:13:03.680 --> 00:13:05.910
isn't going to make
your crypto go up.

00:13:08.480 --> 00:13:11.650
At this point,
should I find another income source?

00:13:13.660 --> 00:13:14.960
Doing what?

00:13:16.530 --> 00:13:18.730
Portable hand sanitizer?

00:13:19.260 --> 00:13:20.430
Masks?

00:13:22.430 --> 00:13:23.870
Listen, I have a gut feeling
about this.

00:13:24.530 --> 00:13:28.500
I feel a huge plague is going to
sweep the nation someday...

00:13:28.570 --> 00:13:31.040
There you go again
with the crazy talk.

00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:34.340
- A plague? Give me a break.
- I'm serious!

00:13:34.410 --> 00:13:37.550
If a specific product doesn't meet
consumer expectations,

00:13:37.610 --> 00:13:39.780
it's only a matter of time
before they drop their subscription.

00:13:39.850 --> 00:13:43.690
It's hard to predict how many people
will even subscribe.

00:13:43.820 --> 00:13:45.890
- As a new business venture,
- Did Eun Sang use her money...

00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:48.690
- the risks seem too high.
- to buy low?

00:13:48.760 --> 00:13:50.160
- What was that?
- Sorry?

00:13:50.230 --> 00:13:51.230
What did you say?

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:53.200
It was nothing.

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:55.530
Okay, so? Go on.

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:57.300
We'd be stuck
if we set everything up...

00:13:57.300 --> 00:13:59.770
and then get too few subscribers.

00:13:59.840 --> 00:14:03.240
Manipulating the budget
and stock is a burden, too.

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:04.910
- But...
- Realistically,

00:14:04.910 --> 00:14:07.180
there's no compelling reason
for a subscription service...

00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:10.110
of snacks you can buy
at any convenience store.

00:14:10.180 --> 00:14:13.020
That's why I think
we need to rethink this...

00:14:13.080 --> 00:14:16.220
and take a step back
to reconsider it objectively.

00:14:16.290 --> 00:14:18.320
Yes, I agree.

00:14:18.820 --> 00:14:21.690
- I was thinking the same thing.
- All right, in that case,

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:24.330
let's all think this over
from every angle.

